                    <death when="0615" syriaca-computed-start="0615-01-01" source="#bib1250-2">0615</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1250-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1250-2">Bedjan, Jab-Alaha, 416- 571 ; BHO, 323.
Trad. (extrait) Chabot, Synodicon orientale, 625- 34; resume par Hoffmann, Ausziige,
91- 115.
Liber castitatis, n° 57.
Chronique de Seert, II, 217- 19.
BSO, I, 1091- 92 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1250">George of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/100">Izla</placeName> was a monk and a convert from
          Zoroastrianism. His name was Mihrangusnap. He was noted for his conversations with the
          Monophysites and opposition to Gabriel of Sinjar, a convert from the Dyophysites to the
          Monophysites. Gabriel condemned George to shah Kusro for leaving his Zoroastrianism, and
          thus George of Izla was put to death.</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1250-1" source="#bib1250-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Gewargīs is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/901">George the Priest (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
